==English==
===Noun===
'''[[just]] [[deserts]]'''
#{{idiom}} A [[punishment]] or [[reward]] that is considered to be what the recipient [[deserve]]d.
#:''It may appear that they're getting ahead by cheating, but they'll get their '''just deserts''' in the end.''

====Usage notes====
*'''Deserts''' here is the plural of [[desert]], meaning "that which one deserves".  It is rarely used outside this phrase.
*The spelling '''just desserts''' is commonly found, but is incorrect, or it is a play on words.

